{
  "stem": "27509.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there, almost overnight, clubs were organized for the-- for the people to have somewhere to come, or where to share, share social contact and to get news, and to discuss things, and so on.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had-- we took-- we took premises.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we organized clubs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And some of the people who played later on a very important part in the-- in the-- people who-- leaders of the-- of the Polish Jewry were part-- members of this club.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And later on, members of these created the Israeli government-- Kleinbaum, Moshe Kleinbaum, who was, who was later Moshe Sneh.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The first Israeli government was, was, was with us in that-- at that club.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he was the man who went, who went to, to interfere-- to intervene with the Russian ambassador in Kovno because there were a number of people who had Palestinian certificates but couldn't go the rest of the way.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The only way for them to go was via Odessa, the south.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "For that, you needed a transit visa from Russia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it was decided to attempt to persuade the Russian authorities to let us have a transit visa to Russia.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And Kleinbaum went with the editor of the of Kovno, who knew the ambassador, for an audience there, made an application.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And lo and behold, the people got transit visas.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they escaped via Odessa.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they got to Palestine in time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That-- so that was part, part of the-- food was, was not provided there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "People had to, to manage the best way they could on an individual basis.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In fact, for a while, we lived a very, very charming life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was-- it was not yet a big upheaval.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And life in Wilno was still going on normally.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They did-- the restaurants were open.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
